give you away as a guy.

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:28.897 position:50% align:center
I should pick something
that distracts from those.

00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:30.690 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
I just said no.

00:11:30.774 --> 00:11:32.609 position:50% align:center
You've gotten a bit taller, too.

00:11:32.692 --> 00:11:33.860 position:50% align:center
If I remember correctly,

00:11:33.943 --> 00:11:35.779 position:50% align:center
I was the tall one in
our middle school days.

00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:37.614 position:50% align:center
No way, I know I had you beat.

00:11:37.697 --> 00:11:39.115 position:50% align:center
Trust me, I wouldn't forget.

00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.408 position:50% align:center
It was by less than an inch.

00:11:40.492 --> 00:11:41.993 position:50% align:center
[MAKIMURA] That's nothing!
You might as well...

00:11:42.077 --> 00:11:46.956 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] It's odd. This doesn't
feel awkward at all.

00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:48.375 position:50% align:center
[MAKIMURA]
Remember how Motoyama...

00:11:48.458 --> 00:11:52.921 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] It used to bother me
so much. Could it be...

00:11:53.004 --> 00:11:55.006 position:50% align:center
I'll still feel the same.

00:11:56.675 --> 00:11:58.760 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] ...because of
what Sasaki told me?

00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:01.179 position:50% align:center
[MAKIMURA]
And your hands, too! Look!

00:12:01.262 --> 00:12:03.098 position:50% align:center
Put your left hand
up against mine.

00:12:03.181 --> 00:12:04.808 position:50% align:center
Okay, sure.

00:12:07.852 --> 00:12:10.730 position:50% align:center
The bone structure in
your hands is manly enough.

00:12:16.695 --> 00:12:18.071 position:50% align:center
Stop it.

00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:24.536 position:50% align:center
Sorry, Makimura!
I'll see you around!

00:12:26.663 --> 00:12:27.914 position:50% align:center
[MAKIMURA]
Wow...

00:12:27.997 --> 00:12:31.501 position:50% align:center
That expression was amazing!
I have to paint it!

00:12:33.461 --> 00:12:36.548 position:50% align:center
Hey. Slow down.

00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:43.263 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry for
getting in the way.

00:12:43.346 --> 00:12:44.931 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:12:45.015 --> 00:12:48.768 position:50% align:center
You weren't in
the way. Trust me.

00:12:48.852 --> 00:12:52.022 position:50% align:center
We were basically
finished talking.

00:12:52.105 --> 00:12:53.481 position:50% align:center
That's good.

00:12:55.859 --> 00:12:58.486 position:50% align:center
So, I gotta know.

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:01.197 position:50% align:center
You told me before
about a girl you like.

00:13:01.281 --> 00:13:02.532 position:50% align:center
That was her, wasn't it?

00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:03.616 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:13.501 --> 00:13:16.254 position:50% align:center
A girl that I used to like.

00:13:18.089 --> 00:13:22.302 position:50% align:center
But I don't feel that way about
her anymore, as it turns out.

00:13:24.721 --> 00:13:27.515 position:50% align:center
[sighs] Gotcha.

00:13:32.562 --> 00:13:34.689 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Sorry for doing that.

00:13:35.648 --> 00:13:38.651 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] I hope I didn't hurt
you when I pulled you away.

00:13:38.735 --> 00:13:41.321 position:50% align:center
It's fine. That was no big deal.

00:13:41.404 --> 00:13:43.281 position:50% align:center
I mean, I am a guy, remember?

00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:45.408 position:50% align:center
Takes more than that to hurt me.

00:13:45.492 --> 00:13:49.871 position:50% align:center
It has nothing to do with
what your gender is.

00:13:49.954 --> 00:13:52.874 position:50% align:center
I don't want to be rough
with someone I like.

00:14:04.511 --> 00:14:06.763 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Um, Sasaki,

00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:10.433 position:50% align:center
don't just say stuff
like that unexpectedly.

00:14:10.517 --> 00:14:12.352 position:50% align:center
I'm blushing.

00:14:14.145 --> 00:14:15.355 position:50% align:center
Miya--

00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.399 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7E] This is bad!
We missed the train!

00:14:17.482 --> 00:14:20.235 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7F] I was winded
from running up the steps!

00:14:22.112 --> 00:14:23.613 position:50% align:center
Let's hop to it.

00:14:23.697 --> 00:14:24.906 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:14:30.954 --> 00:14:32.288 position:50% align:center
Listen.

00:14:34.708 --> 00:14:36.084 position:50% align:center
When I said that just now,

00:14:36.167 --> 00:14:38.962 position:50% align:center
I wasn't trying to
pressure you to answer.

00:14:40.255 --> 00:14:41.464 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:14:52.851 --> 00:14:55.729 position:50% align:center
[MAKIMURA] The bone structure
in your hands is manly enough.

00:14:56.646 --> 00:14:59.482 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] So, my hands are
masculine at least.

00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:05.989 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Wow, his are way bigger!

00:15:06.072 --> 00:15:07.365 position:50% align:center
Is there something wrong?

00:15:07.449 --> 00:15:10.035 position:50% align:center
Huh? No way,
I've never been better!

00:15:11.745 --> 00:15:13.955 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI'S MOM] You can go home
after you put that out,

00:15:14.039 --> 00:15:16.041 position:50% align:center
and take some bread
with you, too.

00:15:17.167 --> 00:15:19.336 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
That girl I saw.

00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:22.213 position:50% align:center
Mya had a crush on her.

00:15:22.297 --> 00:15:25.216 position:50% align:center
I don't even remember her face.

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:27.635 position:50% align:center
It's a wonderful
morning, isn't it?

00:15:27.719 --> 00:15:29.179 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Huh? I mean, yes.

00:15:29.262 --> 00:15:30.472 position:50% align:center
Yes. Sure is.

00:15:30.555 --> 00:15:35.352 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] But I think
she was smaller than him.

00:15:35.435 --> 00:15:39.022 position:50% align:center
Then again, I guess that makes
sense for a girl and a guy.

00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:42.567 position:50% align:center
She and I were usually
in the same group then.

00:15:42.650 --> 00:15:44.402 position:50% align:center
So, we would always
sit together.

00:15:44.486 --> 00:15:46.112 position:50% align:center
She was really easy to talk to.

00:15:46.196 --> 00:15:47.489 position:50% align:center
Back in middle school,

00:15:47.572 --> 00:15:49.491 position:50% align:center
I heard about my
feminine face all the time,

00:15:49.574 --> 00:15:50.992 position:50% align:center
especially from the girls.

00:15:51.076 --> 00:15:52.577 position:50% align:center
It wasn't malicious,

00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:57.207 position:50% align:center
but still, it just started to
get under my skin after a while.

00:15:58.166 --> 00:16:00.585 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO] She was one of
the people who said it.

00:16:00.669 --> 00:16:03.254 position:50% align:center
I know now that
I misunderstood her.

00:16:03.338 --> 00:16:05.048 position:50% align:center
But after that,
it got more and more

00:16:05.131 --> 00:16:07.759 position:50% align:center
difficult for me
to be around her.

00:16:07.842 --> 00:16:09.636 position:50% align:center
So, that was that.

00:16:11.429 --> 00:16:13.223 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I get it.

00:16:13.306 --> 00:16:15.558 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
He told me about it freely,

00:16:15.642 --> 00:16:19.270 position:50% align:center
so that probably means
he's over the whole thing.

00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:21.773 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Still, though.

00:16:21.856 --> 00:16:24.359 position:50% align:center
Even if he doesn't
like her in that way,

00:16:24.442 --> 00:16:28.113 position:50% align:center
she might have
feelings for him, right?

00:16:28.196 --> 00:16:30.490 position:50% align:center
Damn, this sucks.

00:16:30.573 --> 00:16:34.661 position:50% align:center
I mean, we're already in a new
school term and everything.

00:16:36.955 --> 00:16:39.874 position:50% align:center
Oh, good morning, Sasaki.
I didn't see you.

00:16:39.958 --> 00:16:42.293 position:50% align:center
Hey, how's it going, Kuresawa?

00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:43.920 position:50% align:center
It's kind of early, huh?

00:16:44.004 --> 00:16:46.798 position:50% align:center
What's going on, do you live
around this area or something?

00:16:46.881 --> 00:16:48.258 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA]
No, not exactly.

00:16:48.341 --> 00:16:49.843 position:50% align:center
The hospital
my girlfriend's staying at

00:16:49.926 --> 00:16:51.511 position:50% align:center
is pretty close to here,
that's all.

00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:52.804 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Oh.

00:16:52.887 --> 00:16:55.140 position:50% align:center
I went over there yesterday
to study with her.

00:16:55.223 --> 00:16:58.476 position:50% align:center
But apparently, I left
my notebook in her room.

00:16:58.560 --> 00:17:00.603 position:50% align:center
I'm just going to
pick it up before school.

00:17:00.687 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
That makes sense.

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.442 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] Didn't know his
girlfriend was in the hospital.

00:17:05.525 --> 00:17:07.360 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA] So, are you
working an early shift?

00:17:07.444 --> 00:17:08.319 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:17:08.403 --> 00:17:09.863 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I just assumed.

00:17:09.946 --> 00:17:12.449 position:50% align:center
I saw you working
at a bakery a while back.

00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:14.409 position:50% align:center
I wasn't sure if
I should bother you.

00:17:14.492 --> 00:17:17.412 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Right. My family owns the place.

00:17:17.495 --> 00:17:20.081 position:50% align:center
But I only help
if I wake up early.

00:17:20.165 --> 00:17:22.083 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA]
Wow, that's pretty cool.

00:17:22.167 --> 00:17:24.836 position:50% align:center
I wonder if Miyano
knows about that.

00:17:24.919 --> 00:17:26.463 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
So, do you get a lot of chances

00:17:26.546 --> 00:17:28.089 position:50% align:center
to go visit your girlfriend?

00:17:28.173 --> 00:17:30.216 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA] Yeah, whenever
I don't have club.

00:17:30.300 --> 00:17:33.178 position:50% align:center
I didn't go there
after that fight, either.

00:17:33.261 --> 00:17:34.721 position:50% align:center
Oh yeah.

00:17:34.804 --> 00:17:37.349 position:50% align:center
I never got to thank you
for breaking it up that day.

00:17:37.432 --> 00:17:39.225 position:50% align:center
I'm glad you were there.

00:17:40.727 --> 00:17:43.438 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] It's fine.
Really, don't worry about it.

00:17:43.521 --> 00:17:45.565 position:50% align:center
Besides, I didn't
exactly break it up,

00:17:45.648 --> 00:17:46.900 position:50% align:center
just got my butt kicked.

00:17:46.983 --> 00:17:50.779 position:50% align:center
Anyway. Can I use
the drink machine?

00:17:50.862 --> 00:17:53.490 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] Sure. Oh yeah,
now that you mention it,

00:17:53.573 --> 00:17:56.242 position:50% align:center
what were you and those guys
fighting over to begin with?

00:17:56.326 --> 00:17:57.994 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA]
Well, to be honest,

00:17:58.078 --> 00:18:00.038 position:50% align:center
I should've been
minding my own business.

00:18:00.121 --> 00:18:03.458 position:50% align:center
Wait a sec. You were the one
who started the whole thing?

00:18:03.541 --> 00:18:04.709 position:50% align:center
I got mad.

00:18:04.793 --> 00:18:07.128 position:50% align:center
