each other's girlfriends

00:18:07.212 --> 00:18:10.256 position:50% align:center
and I had just had
a serious argument with mine.

00:18:10.340 --> 00:18:13.510 position:50% align:center
I guess I felt guilty about that
and took it out on them.

00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:16.805 position:50% align:center
I said some things
that were uncalled for.

00:18:16.888 --> 00:18:19.599 position:50% align:center
But it won't happen again,
I can assure you.

00:18:19.683 --> 00:18:22.811 position:50% align:center
My girlfriend got upset.
It was a disaster.

00:18:22.894 --> 00:18:24.979 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it's good
to stay out of fights.

00:18:25.063 --> 00:18:28.066 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] This guy lives and
breathes for his girlfriend!

00:18:28.149 --> 00:18:29.526 position:50% align:center
Oh, and by the way,

00:18:29.609 --> 00:18:31.236 position:50% align:center
do you want to come by
and meet her sometime

00:18:31.319 --> 00:18:33.154 position:50% align:center
when you're not too busy?

00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:36.116 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Nah, I'm good.

00:18:36.199 --> 00:18:38.034 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't want to
impose on you.

00:18:38.118 --> 00:18:41.246 position:50% align:center
We wouldn't mind it,
but all right.

00:18:41.329 --> 00:18:43.748 position:50% align:center
Maybe after she
gets released, okay?

00:18:43.832 --> 00:18:45.750 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Mm-hm!

00:18:45.834 --> 00:18:48.420 position:50% align:center
[KURESAWA] It'd be like
her manga came to life.

00:18:54.217 --> 00:18:56.720 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] Sheesh, I guess
I'm a little on edge.

00:18:56.803 --> 00:18:59.055 position:50% align:center
I usually go back to sleep
in the mornings.

00:18:59.139 --> 00:19:03.435 position:50% align:center
[MIYANO]
Hey, Sasaki! How are you doing?

00:19:03.518 --> 00:19:06.479 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI] Oh, right.
I caught the early train.

00:19:06.563 --> 00:19:08.648 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
Good morning, Mya.

00:19:08.732 --> 00:19:11.192 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
I owe you one, Kuresawa.

00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:12.819 position:50% align:center
You're always
listening to your music

00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.571 position:50% align:center
during the ride
to school, aren't you?

00:19:14.654 --> 00:19:16.740 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Take a listen.

00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:18.033 position:50% align:center
Got some new tunage.

00:19:18.116 --> 00:19:20.702 position:50% align:center
I just added a few
more albums yesterday.

00:19:20.785 --> 00:19:22.328 position:50% align:center
Let's play guess-the-song!

00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:24.372 position:50% align:center
Y'sure? I don't think
we listen to

00:19:24.456 --> 00:19:26.249 position:50% align:center
a lot of the same music, though.

00:19:26.332 --> 00:19:28.585 position:50% align:center
I probably won't be
good at this game.

00:19:28.668 --> 00:19:30.795 position:50% align:center
[SASAKI]
I s'pose that's true.

00:19:30.879 --> 00:19:33.173 position:50% align:center
I'll try to pick out a song
you would recognize then,

00:19:33.256 --> 00:19:34.466 position:50% align:center
